<br>
So what did I do?  I waited until about 36 hours after a patch, logged in, sat down where she spawns, and waited with all my friends until the 50th hour had rolled around.  When she still hadn't shown up, I turned logging on, and went to bed.  Some 6 hours later, she still wasn't up so I checked my log to verify that in the span from 36 to 56 hours she did not spawn.<br>
<br>
I've heard from others that it's not a 48 hour spawn, she's on a 24 hour spawn.  And no, she's on a 52 hour spawn, or 36, or... you get the picture.<br>
<br>
What I'm telling you now is not because I heard it.  It's because I camped her on and off for months before I finally caught her.  I don't recall the exact spawn time for the time I got her, but it doesn't matter.  It is random.  The soonest I've ever heard of is 24 hours, and the longest I've heard is 52 hours.  For me it was somewhere in between.  It's different every time.<br>
<br>
She is still heavily camped on many servers so it's rare to find her actually up.  The thing to do is to make a level 1 dark elf mule and camp it there.  Log in your mule from time to time to check in on her until you finally get lucky.  Remember, that is exactly what everyone else is doing too, so it all comes down to you finding her up before anyone else does.<br>
<br>
I have heard of people camping her round the clock for 50 hours at a stretch.  If you have friends willing to tag-team camp her with you then that's the only way to be sure.  Unless this is the last mob you need to kill, it hardly seems worth it to go to this effort.  As long as you find her up sometime before you get all your other stuff, then she's no hinderance.  Unfortunately, it does seem like she is the bottleneck for a lot of enchanters out there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse & Amway Rep.</span><br>  Posts: 336<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(11/16/01 12:48:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vernia Tomb</span><hr size=1> Isn't this the place that Mellifleur has his e-bay 60 monk FDing under the boss' belly? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ueadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(11/20/01 3:44:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vernia Tomb</span><hr size=1> I think she is a 72 hrs spawn, seen her up many of times, but never had the peeps to kill her.<br>
